text:
Saini bhaiiiiiiiii
Tere liye dil se respect nikalti hain. Mujhe aaj bhi Pizza Hut vala lunch yaad hain jab hum pehli baar campus se ghar jaa rhe they midsem break ke liye. Station pe bhi kaafi der tak tere sath bakchodi kari jab teri train late hogayi thi, tabse tere sath ek connection ban gaya tha. 
Campus main chaapu banna bohot log sikhate hain, but tunhe ek accha insaan banna sikhaya, jo shayad puri life sath rahega. 

Milte rahenge, UPSC ke liye best of luck <3
author: Tushar  Goswamy

text: This guy fucks!
author: Tushar  Goswamy

text:
Hello!!
I feel so lucky to have met you, Shreyash, Pratigya and Pragya during Antaragni of 2017 and receive the best friend circle I could have asked for! From pranking Shreyash on April Fools Day to celebrating almost every birthday together, I can't imagine having such a wholesome college life without you. You and Vatsalya were the first people with whom I would share any major life achievements. Also, I don't think anyone apart from you could have convinced me to dance :-P  -  Silent DJ will always be a memory that I will keep dear to me. I'll miss discussing random The Office episodes and never losing an opportunity to say "Thats what she said" in every conversation possible. 

Hoping that we can do more trips like Udaipur in the future 
Pls give my regards to Jaya Singhvi, Sheila Chaudhary road

“I wish there was a way to know you’re in the good old days, before you’ve actually left them.” – Andy Bernard

Pls Pls Pls adopt a new dog - we can make her meet Bruno :-)
author: Tushar  Goswamy

text: Would Smash
author: Tushar  Goswamy

text:
Bhavjeet bhai!
I think pehli baar ICG winter project ke liye mille they, and I knew it then that we will hit it off! You are one of the most hardworking, smart and talented people that I have met in campus. I remember ek baar ICG project report ke liye KD computer lab main nightout maara tha, and tunhe mujhe motivated rakha tha to complete the work. 
I have always looked up to you for motivation and working hard. AnC was lucky to have you, tujhse better GenSec shayad hi IITK ki history main kabhi aaya ho. 
Baaki bakchodi bhi bohot kaati hain humne - Goa trip was epic thanks to you. Gurgaon main milte rahenge, sath main gedi maarne challenge, with Punjabi music (read Vol 1) on full volume. 

Tussi hi to saade Yaar Anmulle ho!
Sutte phukenge, balle balle
author: Tushar  Goswamy

text:
Bro pura second year tere bharose pass kiya hain maine XD
Jab bhi koi doubt hota tha tere room bhag ke chale jaata tha, bina soche ki tunhe woh course kiya hain ki nahi. Mujhe pura confidence tha ki tu sahi rasta dikhayega, and tunhe har course main bohot zyada help ki. Thank you so much, bhai, for always being there for me and helping me with the silliest doubts. 

Love you lots bhai, and thank you soooooo much.
Zyada bengali aati nahi, but Tomake Bhalobasi bhai <3
author: Tushar  Goswamy

text:
Faizan bhaijan!
I have felt closest to you and Vatsalya on campus, and I have always considered you more like a brother and less like a friend. From enjoying Pronights together in Antaragni 2017 to participating in the Samsung Awards in my first year, I can't imagine having such a fun-filled and fulfilling first year without you. You were always there for me and helped me with all my personal as well as professional problems. Thank you so much for making all my birthdays in campus special by throwing such amazing parties and always being present when I needed you.
Also, thank you so much for hosting all of us during Eid and serving delicious food (Special thanks to aunty for making Veg Biryani :-P)

Woh Cadbury Oreo vapas kardio jo 1st year main li thi :-P
Love you bhai <3
author: Tushar  Goswamy

text:
From that nightout in the library before Poddar ka endsem, to flying Laudasur on the airstrip, I can't imagine surviving aero without you. Bhai teri vajeh se I felt lucky and blessed to have got a branch change in Aero. CPI jaisi bhi aayi, but AE main maaze bohot zyada aaye thanks to you. Last day jab tu room aaya tab kaafi emotional hogaya tha, isiliye bol nahi paaya, but will miss you a lot. 
I have passed most of my AE courses thanks to you, graduation credits main sabse upar tera naam ayega XD.
Milte rahenge, apna US trip ka plan abhi bhi On hain. Plus Chennai se to tera ghar zyada dur nahi :-P

Ni A*** Denge

Ravi bhaiiiii
You are the first person I met outside my wing in Campus, and the last person I met (outside my wing) before leaving campus for Home. Almost all major fun events and bakchodiya that I have done in the campus have been with you - from crazy Antaragni nights to first college trip. Holi bhi sath hi main manayi thi XD
Dharamsala and Udaipur have been the highlights of my college life, and both of these trips were with you.
Lets plan the next trip asap!!

Milte rahenge - Stay in touch bhai

Yash Bro!
My book buddy - I always look forward to having meaningful conversations with you. I feel super lucky to know a fellow book lover like you who's always so passionate about discussing literature. I have had some of my most thought-provoking and intellectual discussions on campus with you, and I will always cherish those conversations. 
Your drive to pursue entrepreneurship is admirable, and I hope that you get to pursue it someday.

Best of Luck <3
